nship between giving-up densities and nest predation, which was probably the result of large-scale differences in resource abun- dance between plots. Our study demonstrates how linking theoretical development to the use of empirical behavioral indicators can help determine the relevant ecological scales and processes necessary for understanding predator-prey interactions.},
